Cebu, Digital, JG Summit, Robinsons: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-31T00:41:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/cebu-digital-jg-summit-robinsons-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 3 percent to
4,023.74.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  : The largest Philippine budget
carrier bought back 1 million of its own shares in the open
market, a stock exchange filing showed. The stock increased 1.9
percent to 79 pesos.  JG Summit Holdings Inc. (JGS)  : The stock’s 12-month
price estimate was increased to 30.50 pesos from 24 pesos and
its rating was kept at “buy,” according to Erwin Balita, an
analyst at SB Equities Inc., citing gains from the sale of its
unit Digital Telecommunications Philippines Inc. (DGTL PM). JG
Summit rose 3.5 percent to 25.35 pesos. Digital decreased 15
percent to 1.56 pesos.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : The ‘Ba1’
foreign-currency bond rating of the nation’s largest phone
company will not be affected by its purchase of Digital Telecom,
Moody’s Investors Service said in a statement yesterday. The
stock increased 16 percent to 2,356 pesos.  Robinsons Land Corp. (RLC)  : The nation’s second-largest
shopping mall operator will spend 41 percent of the 13.6 billion
pesos ($313 million) it will raise from a rights offer on land
acquisitions, a stock exchange filing showed. The developer will
use 44 percent of the proceeds, or about 5.96 billion pesos, to
build malls, homes and apartments, it said. The stock fell 0.4
percent to 11.46 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  